    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Mikhail Mikhailovich Solov'ev<br />
(Born Moscow, 1905; died Moscow, 1990)<br />
Aleksandr Alekseevich Zharov<br />
(Born Semenovskaia, 1904; died Moscow, 1984)<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>Be Calm, Soviet Soldier!</em>, TASS No. 0782, August 10, 1943</h3>

    <p>
    Stencil<br />    1690 x 1310 mm<br />    The Soviet soldier is always ready<br />
To tell his friends the news from home.<br />
His family says: "Be calm<br />
Soldier, for home and for family."<br />
<br />
1. <br />
Your wife brings victory closer<br />
With her efficient labor.<br />
<br />
2. <br />
Your children at home<br />
Go to nursery school in the morning.<br />
<br />
3. <br />
Your friends and neighbors <br />
Take care of your garden.<br />
<br />
4. <br />
The mailman brings to your house<br />
Your social subsidy without delay.<br />
<br />
5. <br />
Timurovites in housekeeping,<br />
They help your family all they can.<br />    Ne boltai! Collection, Obj: 205863</p>
        
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

